<TITLE> We won't shield terrorists: PM to OIC chief </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 3 (bdnews24.com)Prime minister Sheikh Hasina, meeting the visiting OIC chief on Tuesday, reaffirmed that Bangladesh would not harbour terrorists. Ekmeleddin Ihsanoglu, secretary-general of the Organisation of the Islamic Conference, met with Hasina on his arrival in Dhaka on a three-day visit. "Mentioning Bangladesh's stance in the fight against terrorism, the prime minister said Bangladesh territory would not be used to launch terrorist activities," the prime minister's deputy press secretary Mahbubul Haque Shakil told reporters after the meeting. Ihsanoglu will meet with president Zillur Rahman and high-ranking government officials during his stay, says a statement of the OIC. The secretary-general is visiting at the invitation of foreign minister Dipu Moni. The OIC chief is also scheduled to attend a convocation of the Islamic University of Technology in Gazipur. He is also expected to visit Dhaka University and deliver a talk on 'OIC's Vision Meeting the Challenges for the 21st Century'. bd
